The paper deals with the problem of Wi-Fi channel assignment, which is a topic in computer networks and falls under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category. The paper also introduces and explores a family of vertex-coloring problems, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and falls under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. The paper uses concepts from information theory, such as the notion of interference threshold, which falls under the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper also uses graph theory and algorithms, which fall under the cs.AL (Algorithms) category. Finally, the paper discusses experimental results, which could fall under the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category.
